name: The Cars That Made the World
original_name: The Cars That Made the World
overview: Telling the story of a group of rival engineers who created the most transformative invention of the 20th century, this docuseries explores over a century of innovation from Honda, Toyota, Mercedes, Ford, Porsche, Rolls Royce and more.

episodes.name: Fueling Invention
episodes.overview: Frustrated by the limitations of transport, rival engineers Karl Benz and Gottlieb Daimler set out to liberate humanity from their dependence on the horse.

episodes.name: Create a Market, Build an Empire
episodes.overview: As early car-makers gained traction with their inventions, the outbreak of the First World War One catapulted the industry into a new era of competition.

episodes.name: Motorise the Masses
episodes.overview: As the roaring twenties brought cars to the masses in America, Europe lagged far behind, and Japan struggled to modernise. Changes came with the Second World War.

episodes.name: Winning the World Over
episodes.overview: In the 1950s America entered a golden age of car design, while German and Japanese car makers struggled to recover from the Second World War.
